review_blob: Lovely spicy dark full bodied bitter. So close to that perfect northern ale, Icannot believe its an ASDA bottle.  Well done asda and well done WHitechapel
Dark and Golden in colour, very little body or head.  Nicely bitter in taste with a bit too much citric flavour after the caramel..
Nice colour, but thin in body.  Nice bitter taste maybe too much for some.  Drinks while room temperature as well as cold.
The marmite beer - like it or loathe it!  I like the cherry flavour and aftertones.  Colour and body is all there.
Beautiful dark full bodied ale.  Just the thing to savour with a lovely salty snack, but definitely not for the pint!
Hope it was a one off but this bottle died on me.  Very gassy on pour but went flat very quick.  Needs chilling and drinking quick, not a beer to be savoured.
This needs to be more freely available and I cannot believe its not on the top 50, I am going to have try drink the rest to see why!
